UK Says no British Planes Fired on in Iraq
LONDON , December 28 ( Xinhua ) -- Britain said on Monday that its aircraft were not involved in an incident in northern Iraq in which the U.S. war planes opened fire after being attacked by Iraqi anti-aircraft forces .
" There were no British involvement , " a British defense ministry spokesman said , confirming at the same time that U.S. aircraft came under attack in Iraq " and they responded to being attacked . "
He said all the U.S. planes returned to base safely .
